[Date: Tue, 10 Jan 2023 23:43:53 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: john.nash@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <1448326334.439.1673394233820@49563c82eb89> Subject: Miss Bz Patient 2 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_436_549499841.1673394233807" ------=_Part_436_549499841.1673394233807 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_437_208988171.1673394233807" ------=_Part_437_208988171.1673394233807 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_438_1362959046.1673394233807" ------=_Part_438_1362959046.1673394233807 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr John Nash, Miss Bz Patient 2 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Miss Bz Patient 2 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-11/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=3YHo0TZwRs Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-11/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=3YHo0TZwRs 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Miss Bz Patient 2 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-11/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_438_1362959046.1673394233807 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr John Nash,

Miss Bz Patient 2 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Miss Bz Patient 2

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-11/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=3YHo0TZwRs

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-11/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=3YHo0TZwRs
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Miss Bz Patient 2 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-11/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team
